    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey @Cuteivist, @saledjenic is correct, the validation in the add flow should match that in the edit flow. Both flows should allow the user to add a space in the account name.\r\n\r\nThe things we validate against that are not allowed are:\r\n- Name length >20 chars \r\n- Use of special characters \r\n- Use of emojis\r\n- Where the name, emoji and colour of account are all the same as another account\r\n\r\n`Wallet v2` desktop designs (where we detail the account name validation in full)\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=12322-276497&t=FtIXdCmy5P9mwadY-4\r\n\r\nThe mobile designs follow the desktop designs on this and should be consistent (I see a couple of validation states currently missing in the mobile designs but when they are taken into the UI design phase these should be added).\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/Q92CTbwanXZwSWrHWKfJqS/Wallet-UX-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=3258-493247&t=NW34ozUYZ14epE2Z-4\r\n\r\nThe user can change the account name from wallet settings as well, but we just launch the same edit dialog shown in the `Wallet v2` file - so in the settings file, we just link back to `Wallet v2`:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/idUoxN7OIW2Jpp3PMJ1Rl8/%E2%9A%99%EF%B8%8F-Settings-%7C-Desktop?type=design&node-id=15264-365634&t=fCeOLj4DMXZznv0z-4\r\n\r\nHope that helps clarify @Cuteivist , just shout if not :)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1850\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-05 at 09 47 18\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/fd770e44-d6c5-436d-998f-2f06ea14fc2c\">\r\n",
